data.title: Renault Company History
data.meta_description: With over 120 years in the automotive industry, Renault has a proud history and heritage tracing back to 1898 in Voiturette, France. Find out more about the reliable and magifique automobiles built under the Renault Revolution and the brand's growing reputation in New Zealand and around the globe.
data.text:
In 1975 Renault Sport was formed, a division of the company that focused on motorsport and performance vehicles. It was not long before Renault entered the world of Formula 1 with the introduction of the RS01 in 1977. A 'magnifique' edition to Formula 1, the new vehicle featured a dual turbo charged engine, a first in in the sports long history.

This was the start of a long career in F1 for Renault, going on to win 5 drivers titles and 6 constructors championships with team Williams and Benneton through the 90s.
